HAM8 uses 8 bit planes. 6 bitplanes are used for the base colours (and that is why you get a 64
colour palette) and the modify values, the 2 remaining bitplanes are used for the control
(normal, modify red, modify green, modify blue.

Normal HAM is similar but uses 6 bitplanes (4 for colour, 2 for control).

