Ciao Steve Hargreaves,

>Does anyone know where I can find some good info on search algorithms
>(searching within a selection of text files)? I'm after speeding something
>up.

 If the texts are alphabetically ordered, you can use the so called
"binary search" . It is the based on the algorithm used in QuickSort.
 It is very fast and if your texts aren't alphabetically ordered, you
could think to order them first and use this algorithm (you have to
check if that is useful, though).

 Here it is an example I did in TurboPascal (but you can easy convert
to Blitz). You need to put all your texts in an array called vet[1..100]
, the text to search is in "j".

[...]

j:="Text to search";
c:=0;
inf:=1;
sup:=n; ->number of texts

while (c=0) do
begin
    center:=(inf+sup) / 2;

    if (j=vet[center]) or (inf=center) then
    begin
        c:=1;
    end;

    if j<vet[center] then
    begin
        sup:=center;
    end
    else
    begin
        inf:=center;
    end;
end;

writeln;
if j=vet[centro] then writeln('Found.')
else writeln('Not found.);

[...]

Hope to have been usefull. :)


