Here is the example from BUM4 (I only have it on paper, that is why it is not on the site
ATM), see the online help for a description of what the fields do
(blitz2:redhelp/acidguides/speaklib.guide).

NEWTYPE.voicepars
flags.b
f0enthusiasm:f0perturb
f1adj:f2adj:f3adj
a1adj:a2adj:a3adj
articulate:centralize:centphon$
avbias.b:afbias:priority:pad1
End NEWTYPE

*v.voicepars = VoiceLoc ; Set up pointer to point to return value
*v\flags=1
*v\f0enthusiasm=82,90 ; old aged highly excited voice
*v\f1adj=0,0,0 ; these are fun to mess with
*v\a1adj=0,0,0
*v\centralize=50,"AO" ; no effect
*v\articulate=90
*v\avbias=20,20

Speak "COME ON EVERYBODY, DANCE? boom boom you like my body yes!"

End

